# git-commit skill

Execute git commits following the conventional commit specification. Analyzes the
staged/unstaged diff, infers the commit type (feat, fix, refactor, docs, test,
chore, build, ci, perf, style) and scope from the changed files, then composes a
concise commit message that explains the *why* rather than the *what*.
